    Course IDCourse Description Location Timestamp
    13046 This course is designed to give students an introduction to financial accounting and reporting concepts, including an overview of the accounting cycle, financial statements, related disclosures, and the ethical responsibility of accountants in business. Students will be expected to demonstrate proficiency in applying technical concepts to selected homework problems. Students will also need to demonstrate writing proficiency in their assignments. course-description\main.js 2018-06-15T15:29:50-06:00

    Account Classification Quiz This is a timed assessment. This quiz assesses your understanding of the account names and classifications being used this semester. AFTER YOU ANSWER THE FIRST QUESTION AND MOVE FORWARD IN THE ASSESSMENT, YOUWILL NOTBE PERMITTED TO RETURN TO ANY PRIOR QUESTION. ANSWER EACH QUESTION COMPLETELY AND FINALLY BEFORE MOVING FORWARD TO THE NEXT QUESTION. 336bbbe5a0ceefa8b13ea18298571ff5281444 The following questions require you to match account names with their proper financial statement classification. Partial credit is given on each question. However, wrong answers eliminate 1-for-1 credit given for correct answers. quiz-instructions\main.js 2018-06-15T15:25:57-06:00
    SEC Quiz You are to use ONLY the SEC.gov website to answer the questions of this assessment. Once initiated, you have FOUR HOURSto complete this assessment.It cannot be saved or continued later. Further, questions must be answered in the order presented. After a question is answered and you have moved forward to the next question, you will NOT be permitted to return to any prior questions. quiz-instructions\main.js 2018-06-15T15:25:57-06:00
    Accounting Cycle XC This assessment covers materials learned in Chapters 1 through 4 of the Textbook. This assessment is opened-book and notes (including the project spreadsheet). However, it is to be completedindividually without the help of any other individual or resource. Start the assessment. Prior to the first question of the assessment will be instructions that must be followed prior to answering any questions of the assessment. You have TWO ATTEMPTS to complete this extra credit assessment. Your score will be the averageof the two attempts. However, in order to move forward on to a second attempt, you must score a minimum of 30% on the first attempt. The more difficult questions receive heavier weight. TO OBTAIN ANY CREDIT, YOU MUST SUBMIT YOUR COMPLETED EXCEL WORKSHEETS SUPPORTING THE ANSWERS YOU ENTERED ON THE FINAL ATTEMPT OF THE ASSESSMENT. quiz-instructions\main.js 2018-06-15T15:25:57-06:00
    Bank Reconciliation XC This assessment is opened-book and notes (including spreadsheets). However, it is to be completedindividually without the help of any other individual or resource. Begin the assessment, complete the instructions in the problem, and answer the questions in the assessment. You have TWOATTEMPTS to complete this extra credit assessment. Your score will be the averageof the twoattempts. However, in order to move forward to a second attempt, you must score a minimum of 40% on the first attempt. The more difficult questions receive heavier weight. quiz-instructions\main.js 2018-06-15T15:25:57-06:00
    Bond Issuance XC This assessment is opened-book and notes (including spreadsheets). However, it is to be completedindividually without the help of any other individual or resource. You have TWOATTEMPTS to complete this extra credit assessment. Your score will be the averageof the twoattempts. However, in order to move forward on to a second attempt, you must score a minimum of 40% on the first attempt. Each question receives equal weight. Included in this assessmentare two independent fact situations.Using these facts, complete effective interest amortization schedules for each company and answer the questions contained in the assessment. quiz-instructions\main.js 2018-06-15T15:25:57-06:00
    Cashflows XC This assessment is opened-book and notes (including spreadsheets developed in class). However, it is to be completedindividually without the help of any other individual or resource. However, in order to move forward on to a second attempt, you must score a minimum of 30% on the first attempt. More difficult questions receive greater weight. quiz-instructions\main.js 2018-06-15T15:25:57-06:00
